configurations.help_text: The Hunt Score equation is used to prioritize events within Threat Vectors. Under the Default view you may change the name of contributing functions, as well as the weight that they hold in generating the Hunt Score. Click 'Advanced' for more options on how to construct a Hunt Equation.
configurations.name: hunt_equation
configurations.value: contribute(numberOf('files.flags'),'Content Analyzer Flags',[0,3],2.0) + contribute(exists('intel.providers'),'Intel Corroboration',[0,5],1.0) + contribute(flagFreq('meta.host'),'Repeatedly Suspicious Host',[0,1],1.0) + contribute(min(1, 1 / (count('meta.host') + 0.00001)),'Host Rarity',[0,5],3.0) + contribute(valueOf('analysis.huri.result.confidence'),'Suspicious Looking Hostname',[0,2],1.0) + contribute(contains('meta.app','smtp') * contains('files.filetype','executable'),'Executable Attachment ',[0,2],1.0) + contribute(1 - contains('meta.host', ['.org','.com','.net','.edu','.gov','.us']),'Uncommon Top Level Domain',[0,2],1.0) + contribute(between(count('files.sha256'), 5, 30),'Potential Targeted Campaign',[0,2],1.0) + contribute(gte(count('files.sha256'), 100),'Potential Spam Campaign',[0,2],1.0)
